    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix division by zero and improve space utilization in textlist widget\n\n### Summary\nThe textlist widget's allocate() function had potential division by zero issues and was not making optimal use of available space. This fix addresses these problems while ensuring proper repaint behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/textlist.c`: \n  - Added division by zero protection in allocate() and button() functions\n  - Improved space utilization by including partial lines when there's space available\n  - Added DIRTY event trigger to ensure visual updates after allocation\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may experience crashes or unexpected behavior when:\n1. Textlist widgets are allocated with very small heights (less than line height)\n2. The X11 backend returns invalid line height values\n3. Widget resizing operations don't trigger visual updates\n\nSymptoms include application crashes due to division by zero, or textlist widgets not displaying content properly after resize operations.\n"
}